OL,3,COver 100,000 people left without power
OL,4,Cin France heatwave
OL,6,FFrance recorded its hottest day ever
OL,7,Fon Tuesday with temperatures in Pissos
OL,8,Fin the south west reaching a scorching
OL,9,F44.3C.
OL,11,FAn average temperature, measured
OL,12,Facross 30 weather stations, reached a
OL,13,Fnew high of 29.8C, hotter than the
OL,14,Fprevious record in 2019.
OL,16,FSpeaking after a crisis meeting on
OL,17,FMonday, French Prime Minister
OL,18,FSebastien Lecornu said that 40 people
OL,19,Fhad drowned in the hot weather in the
OL,20,Flast five days. Many of the victims
OL,21,Fwere young people, he added.
